# ============================================================
#  COMPLIANCE NOTES
#
#  GDPR  (EU)    — Protects any data identifying EU residents.
#                  Never commit names, emails, IPs, cookies,
#                  device IDs, or inferred personal attributes.
#
#  CCPA  (CA)    — Covers California residents. Treat any
#                  consumer identifier (incl. pseudonymous)
#                  as protected.
#
#  HIPAA (US)    — 18 PHI identifiers must never be stored in
#                  code repos (names, DOB, geo <3 digits, etc.)
#
#  PCI-DSS       — Card numbers, CVVs, and auth data must never
#                  appear in source control under any encoding.
#
#  SOC 2         — Audit logs and access records should be
#                  stored in secure, access-controlled systems,
#                  not in git history.
#
#  Best practice — Treat your git history as public. If a
#                  secret or PII ever gets committed, rotate
#                  the credential and use git filter-repo to
#                  scrub the history before next push.
# ============================================================
